03/04/2009
TIRANA, Albania -- European commission (EC) Director-General for Enlargement Michael Leigh announced on Thursday (April 2nd) during a two-day Balkans donors' conference in Tirana that the EU has prepared a 750m euro anti-crisis package to help the Balkan countries. The package includes 150m euros under the so-called Pre-Accession Instrument and about 600m euros to be granted through international financial institutions. Nearly 200 representatives of international financial institutions attended the Tirana conference. (Top News, Balkan Web, Shekulli - 02/04/09)
